        <heading>892.2.  Notice of controlled dangerous substance conviction; licensing authority</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 892.2.  Notice of controlled dangerous substance conviction; licensing authority
When a person is convicted of violating any felony provision of the Uniform Controlled Dangerous Substances Law, the court imposing sentence shall determine if the defendant possesses a license to practice a trade, occupation, or profession in this state and, if so, the court shall cause notice of the conviction to be forwarded to the appropriate licensing authority.</p>
        </content>
